%% Sequence-Diagramm: Ein Client legt eine Booking (Sales Person → Slot @ Datum) an.
%% Zeigt Auth-Weitergabe, TX-Öffnung, Permission-Check und Cascade zu Booking-Log.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as Client (Frontend)
    participant REST as REST-Handler<br/>rest/booking.rs
    participant BookingSvc as BookingService<br/>service_impl/booking.rs
    participant Perm as PermissionService
    participant TX as TransactionDao
    participant BookingDao as BookingDao
    participant LogSvc as BookingLogService
    participant DB as SQLite

    User->>+REST: POST /booking<br/>{sales_person_id, slot_id, date}
    Note over REST: Session-Middleware liefert<br/>Authentication<Context>
    REST->>+BookingSvc: create(dto, auth, tx=None)
    BookingSvc->>+TX: use_transaction(None)
    TX->>DB: BEGIN
    TX-->>-BookingSvc: tx
    BookingSvc->>+Perm: require_role(auth, ShiftplanEdit)
    Perm-->>-BookingSvc: Ok / Err(Forbidden)
    Note over BookingSvc: Konflikt-Check:<br/>bestehende Booking? Absence?
    BookingSvc->>+BookingDao: find_conflict(sales_person, date, tx)
    BookingDao->>DB: SELECT ... WHERE deleted IS NULL
    BookingDao-->>-BookingSvc: []
    BookingSvc->>+BookingDao: insert(booking, created_by=auth.user, tx)
    BookingDao->>DB: INSERT
    BookingDao-->>-BookingSvc: BookingEntity
    BookingSvc->>+LogSvc: log_create(booking, auth, tx)
    LogSvc->>DB: INSERT booking_log
    LogSvc-->>-BookingSvc: Ok
    BookingSvc->>+TX: commit(tx)
    TX->>DB: COMMIT
    TX-->>-BookingSvc: Ok
    BookingSvc-->>-REST: Booking
    REST-->>-User: 201 Created<br/>BookingTO

    Note over BookingSvc,DB: Bei Fehler in irgendeinem Schritt:<br/>TX rollt zurück, keine Zombie-Zeilen.
